Churches are waiting for government to announce if restrictions on gatherings will be tightened. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Charismatic churches are calling on the government to recognise the importance of connection at Easter. Many churches want worshippers to spend this religious holiday in church and not at home via online streaming. The presiding Bishop of Grace Bible Church, Mosa Sono, says many people are lacking spiritually and are depressed. "The number of people who are struggling with depression, family breakdown, a lack of being serviced spiritually is high." Charismatic churches are calling on govt to recognise the importance of connection at Easter. It wants worshippers to spend this religious holiday in church and not at home via online streaming.#DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/kvnihaByzL Meanwhile, the Health Department reported 1,387 new COVID-19 infections in the last 24 hours. Sadly, 46 more people have died due to COVID-19 complications. READ: COVID-19 | It is everyone's responsibility, says new MAC co-chair South Africa's death toll is at 52,648. SA's recovery rate is at 95%.